<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Prunus virginiana</i> can be top-killed by fire but will resprout prolifically. Seed germination is also improved by heat, which may add to postfire regeneration. Following fire, <i>P. virginiana</i> shrubs appear to generally increase in number and density before returning to prefire condition after a number of years (Johnson 2000c).</div>
